VARIABLES
	- objects stores its state in fields, called variables
	- Instance Variables (Non-Static Fields) - unique to each instance of a class (to each object, in other words)
	- Class Variables (Static Fields)- one copy of this variable in existence, regardless of how many times the class has been instantiated.
	- Local Variables - the variable is declared â€” which is between the opening and closing braces of a method
	- Parameters  - variable is the parameter to this method 
	
PRIMITIVES
	- byte, short, int, long
	- float, double
	- boolean, char, String
	- default values - 0, 0, 0, 0L, 0.0f, 0.0d, '\u0000', false, null
	
ARRAYS
	-  a container object that holds a fixed number of values of a single type
	
OPERATORS
	- 
	
EXPRESSIONS, STATEMENTS, BLOCKS
	- An expression is a construct made up of variables, operators, and method invocations
	- A statement forms a complete unit of execution
	- A block is a group of zero or more statements between balanced braces
	
FLOW STRUCTURES
	- if, if else, switch
	- while, for
	- break, continue
